article.headline: Texas A&amp,M-Corpus Christi 84, St. Edward's 70
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas -- Five players scored in double digits and Demond Watt scored 19 points to led the way in an 84-70 Texas A&M-Corpus Christi victory over St. Edward's on Wednesday night. Watt also had eight rebounds and two blocked shots for the Islanders (4-3). Justin Reynolds and Kevin Palmer each scored 16; LaMarr Drake and Filip Toncinic added 11. Reggie Shanks was the leading scorer for St. Edward's (4-2). He scored 13 points and had six rebounds in the game. Taylor Mullenax and Tylor Carr each had 12 for the Hilltoppers. The Islanders outscored St. Edward's 33-10 from the free throw line.
